This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the accurate detection of lane and road markings in images. It also involves the use of convolutional neural networks for semantic segmentation. 

It could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the accurate detection of lane and road markings is important for intelligent vehicles. 

The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The use of Fully Convolutional Networks and Spatial Transformer Networks suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper deals with the security of autonomous vehicles, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
